{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "66bcc016ae81d148616b2684", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 30, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d70f9a489afa3080ade2d"], "chapters": ["615d6ff22b295b085ab6ec13"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "64b850042a7d64ecd80b00b9", "title": "NEET 2020 (Phase 2)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "According to Alexander von Humboldt:", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "W8Kp1", "text": "Species richness decreases with increasing area of exploration", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "VVYyg", "text": "Species richness increases with increasing area, but only up to limit", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "KdFj7", "text": "There is no relationship between species richness and area explored.", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "RbDDe", "text": "Species richness goes on increasing with increasing area of exploration", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>German naturalist and geographer Alexander von Humboldt while exploring the South American jungles, found that within a region species richness increased with increasing explored area but only up to a limit. The relationship between species richness and area turned out to be a rectangular hyperbola for a wide variety of organisms. The relationship is a straight line on a logarithmic scale.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>CA</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi></msup></math></p><p>Applying logarithm on both sides:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>logS</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>logC</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>ZlogA</mi></math></p><p>where,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math>&nbsp;= Species richness<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> = Area<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi></math>&nbsp;= Slope of the line (regression coefficient)<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>&nbsp; = Y&ndash;intercept</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "ques_type": "Correct Statement", "masterId": "MOGNEPYQ14334237", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "bucket": "", "isRemoved": false, "updatedAt": "2024-09-02T07:41:21.802Z", "updated_by": "65d0c176a8f74604505ba6f6", "cpyqbSubjects": ["616057290283de43c87e3e1a", "616057b00283de43c87e3e20", "64d50cd33df7f4a7f3017f71", "66b79bbbd4b564dfab4f94d2", "67fa60d64468eb1307ceb0b0", "6807d392647479b8e869647c"], "cpyqbChapters": ["616025f1471a25fb7be4daa7", "616025f2e905bdc7d82bbba9", "64eb06d53118f713ecfef15e", "66d58552a75f05ee8564f65e", "67fdff52378e1624ea7b6a2a", "68091fdf3a10446a207fdbc1"], "cpyqbExams": ["616059d70283de43c87e3e24", "616059730283de43c87e3e22"]}, "fetch_status": true}